## Error 3: `log.topoSet` — Unknown set type `cellZone`

The `topoSetDict` references `cellZone` as a set type, but in OpenFOAM 10, `cellZone` is not a valid set type. The valid set types are `cellSet`, `cellZoneSet`, `faceSet`, `faceZoneSet`, `pointSet`, `pointZoneSet`.

### Root Cause
The `topoSetDict` has:
```
{
    name    obstacle;
    type    cellZone;
    action  new;
    source  setToCellZone;
    sourceInfo
    {
        set obstacleCell;
    }
}
```

In OpenFOAM 10, `setToCellZone` with a `cellSet` source creates a `cellZoneSet`, not a `cellZone`. The `type` should be `cellZoneSet`, not `cellZone`.

### Solution
**Modify `topoSetDict`** to change the `type` from `cellZone` to `cellZoneSet`:

```
actions
(
    {
        name    obstacleCell;
        type    cellSet;
        action  new;
        source  boxToCell;
        sourceInfo
        {
            box (0.5 0 0) (0.5625 0.1875 1);
        }
    }

    {
        name    obstacle;
        type    cellZoneSet;
        action  new;
        source  setToCellZone;
        sourceInfo
        {
            set obstacleCell;
        }
    }
);
```

This creates a `cellZoneSet` called `obstacle`, which is a valid set type in OpenFOAM 10. The `subsetMesh` command will then be able to use this `cellZoneSet` to create the new `obstacle` patch.

